More trouble in the Nasarawa State chapter of the ruling All Progressive Congress (APC) as Honourable Abdulaziz Danladi, member representing Keffi East Constituency at the Nasarawa State House of Assembly, has officially dumped APC for Action Alliance (AA) Rt. Hon Ibrahim Balarabe Abdullahi, the Speaker of the House made this known while reading Hon. Abdulaziz’s resignation letter during the House sitting in Lafia. The speaker said that based on the letter, Abdulaziz has joined Action Alliance ( AA). “This is a letter from Hon Abdulaziz SK Danladi, member representing Keffi East Constituency informing the House of his resignation from APC. “The letter read as thus, Notice of Change of Party. I wish to formally inform the House of my resignation from the All Progressives Congress ( APC). ” This is due to internal party issues which the party is yet to resolve. Recall that the House member contested the House representative seat under the platform of APC but lost to his opponent at the primary recently conducted in the state.